content:
To calculate the number of times a specific character appears in a string, you can use a simple method in many programming languages. Here's how you can do it in a few different languages:

### Python
You can use the `count()` method which is built into Python strings.

```python
string = "Mary had a little lamb"
character = 'a'
count = string.count(character)
print(count)  # Output will be 4
```

### JavaScript
You can split the string into an array using the character and then find the length difference of the array.

```javascript
let string = "Mary had a little lamb";
let character = 'a';
let count = string.split(character).length - 1;
console.log(count);  // Output will be 4
```

### Java
You can iterate over the characters in the string and count how many times the character appears.

```java
public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        String string = "Mary had a little lamb";
        char character = 'a';
        int count = 0;

        for (int i = 0; i < string.length(); i++) {
            if (string.charAt(i) == character) {
                count++;
            }
        }

        System.out.println(count);  // Output will be 4
    }
}
```

### C++
You can iterate through each character in the string and count occurrences.

```cpp
#include <iostream>
#include <string>
using namespace std;

int main() {
    string str = "Mary had a little lamb";
    char character = 'a';
    int count = 0;

    for (char c : str) {
        if (c == character) {
            count++;
        }
    }

    cout << count << endl;  // Output will be 4
    return 0;
}
```

These examples should give you a good starting point for counting characters in a string using different programming languages.
